default1.4 The government has completely failed to deliver on its pledge to make more central and local governme
defaultnt services available at post offices.
default&#xa0;
default1.5 Instead, post offices are highly and increasingly dependent on income from Royal Mail services for their survival.
default&#xa0;
default1.6 Since separation, subpostmasters are already experiencing a more aggressive attitude from Ro
defaultyal Mail towards post offices.
default&#xa0;
default1.7 The NFSP fears that a privatised Royal Mail will seek to 
defaultfurther 
defaultreduce costs and increase profits by renegotiating its business agreement with POL.
default&#xa0;
default1.8 POL and the post office network will be unable to survive 
defaultindependently from Royal Mail Group
default. The
default NFSP is 
defaulttherefore 
defaultcalling for the
default government to halt the privatis
defaultation of Royal Mail; and to retain an ongoing stake in the company to defend the interests of our post offices.
